HEADWORD: Nomancy
<hw>No"man*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>nomancie</ets>, <ets>nomance</ets>, abbrev. fr.
<ets>onomancie</ets>. See <er>Onomancy</er>.]</ety> <def>The art or
practice of divining the destiny of persons by the letters which form
their names.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

